{
  "texts": [
    "Results are summarized in Table 3, where we report the BFs between the templates with and without HMs.",
    "To gauge the impact of the priors, we also show the values of the network optimal signal-to-noise ratio SNR net opt, the information H [178] and the maximum value of the logarithmic likelihood lnL max.",
    "None of the events shows strong preference for HMs.",
    "Nonetheless, the events GW170729, GW190521_074359, GW200129_065458, GW200224_222234 have a low but positive BF.",
    "To appreciate the consequences of this fact, in Fig. 3 we study how the PE on the initial masses m 1,2 varies when HMs are included."
  ]
}